comments: Westbrook (LAC) rests his hand on Watson's (DEN) left arm and immediately removes his hand as Watson enters his upward shooting motion.
Watson (DEN) is moving alongside Harden's (LAC) path and Harden loses control of his dribble on his own.
Watson (DEN) makes clean contact with the ball as he attempts to tie up Harden (LAC).
As Harden (LAC) gains possession, Coach Lue (LAC) attempts to call a timeout, which is not recognized by the crew.
Watson (DEN) cleanly deflects the ball as Harden (LAC) attempts to pass.
Jackson (DEN) gathers the ball on his right foot and does not take more than two steps after his gather.
Leonard (LAC) makes contact with the ball, and the part of Jackson's (DEN) hand that is on the ball, as he defends the driving shot attempt.
Porter Jr. (DEN) moves alongside Leonard's (LAC) path and marginal body contact occurs during the driving shot attempt.
Leonard (LAC) is bracing for the contact from Porter Jr. (DEN) and marginal contact occurs as he releases away from the contact.
George (LAC) legally contests Porter Jr.'s (DEN) jump shot, making "high-five" contact after the ball is released.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the court (successful 2-point basket) was overturned to a successful 3-point basket.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) legally contests George's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAC) cleanly dislodges the ball from Porter Jr. (DEN), and incidental contact occurs as the two players go to the floor in pursuit of the loose ball.
Harden (LAC) avoids making contact with Watson's (DEN) head as he contests the shot near the rim.
Caldwell-Pope (DEN) legally contests George's (LAC) jump shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAC) commits a take foul on Caldwell-Pope (DEN).
